 Summary of Problems
 M3076 / M3079 – RDP Identity Verification Error
 "Remote Desktop cannot verify the identity of the remote computer because there is a time or date difference..."

 Likely Cause:
The system clock on M3076 and M3079 is out of sync with the domain controller.

RDP (and Kerberos) requires accurate time sync (±5 mins max).

 Fix:
On each affected machine:

powershell
Copy
Edit
# Force time sync with domain controller
w32tm /resync /nowait
If it fails, run:

powershell
Copy
Edit
# Reset the time service
net stop w32time
w32tm /unregister
w32tm /register
net start w32time
w32tm /resync
Then retry RDP.

 M3015 – Application Error (FMS Client Cache)
 "The proxy could not locate or start an FMS Client Cache instance..."

 Likely Cause:
This isn't an RDP issue — it's the FMS client app failing to initialise after login.

The error mentions:

FMS_WINDOWS_MULTIUSER not being enabled

FMS_HOME environment variable not set

A missing .dll for the FMS client cache proxy

 Fix:
On M3015, check if it’s a multi-user RDP session host — if yes:

Set environment variable FMS_WINDOWS_MULTIUSER=1

Verify FMS_HOME is correctly defined in system environment variables.

Confirm required *.dll files exist in:

makefile
Copy
Edit
C:\FlexCache\FMSProxy\[64|lib64|dll]\[dlls...]
Check whether the app runs correctly under:

Local login

Other users

Shared account (e.g. shr-)

 Recommendations
